REPORTER: Asterpay dev. REPO: github.com/Godman-s/pact (founder-owned — skingem1).

Two fixes in one PR/commit to that repo:

(a) src/verifier.ts lines 56-60 — replace non-constant-time HMAC compare with crypto.timingSafeEqual. Current:
    const expected = createHmac('sha256', secret).update(hash).digest('hex');
    if (mandate.signature !== expected) { return { valid: false, reason: 'signature mismatch' }; }

  Replace with length-check guarded timing-safe compare:
    const expected = createHmac('sha256', secret).update(hash).digest('hex');
    const sigBuf = Buffer.from(mandate.signature, 'hex');
    const expBuf = Buffer.from(expected, 'hex');
    if (sigBuf.length !== expBuf.length || !timingSafeEqual(sigBuf, expBuf)) {
      return { valid: false, reason: 'signature mismatch' };
    }
  Add import: import { timingSafeEqual } from 'node:crypto'; (already has createHmac — extend the same import).

(b) demo-negotiation.ts line 42 — remove the hard-coded INVOICA_KEY constant. Replace with process.env.INVOICA_API_KEY read and a clear dotenv hint in the file header. Add INVOICA_API_KEY=<your-key-here> to .env.demo.example and ensure .env.demo is in .gitignore.

Note: git history still contains the old key — that's why M1-SEC-HOTFIX-01 (revocation) matters more than the scrub. Do NOT attempt git-filter-repo on a public repo; it rewrites history and breaks anyone who forked. The revocation in HOTFIX-01 is the real fix; the scrub is hygiene.

Commit message: 'security: timing-safe HMAC compare in verifier, env-ify INVOICA_API_KEY (reported by Asterpay dev)'. Push to main.

Acceptance: Godman-s/pact main has the fixed verifier.ts and demo-negotiation.ts. `grep sk_302e` on HEAD returns 0. Node REPL test: verifier rejects tampered signature in constant time (manual smoke test OK).
